Complexul Energetic Rovinari SA, a
state-owned Romanian electricity company, selected China Huadian
Engineering Co. to build a 500-megawatt coal-fired plant, Bursa
 reported , citing unidentified company officials.  Rovinari and the Chinese company will negotiate a
memorandum of understanding by the end of June on the
1 billion-euro ($1.3 billion) project and the plant is likely to
be functional at the end of 2015, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  